1. User Authentication
  Account Management: Allow users to create accounts, log in, and track their personal scores.
  Password Recovery: Implement a password reset feature.
  Profile Management: Allow users to update their profile information.
2. Advanced Scoring and Leaderboards
  Detailed Score Tracking: Track scores by question type or difficulty level.
  Global Leaderboard: Display a global leaderboard showing the top scores of all players.
  Friend Leaderboards: Allow users to compare scores with friends or other users.
3. Question Management
  Add/Remove Questions: Implement an admin interface to add or remove questions from the database.
  Categorized Questions: Organize questions into categories or tags.
  Question Difficulty Levels: Allow users to select questions based on difficulty.
4. Game Modes
  Timed Challenges: Add a timed mode where users answer questions under time constraints.
  Multiplayer Mode: Implement a multiplayer mode where users can compete against each other in real-time.
  Practice Mode: Provide a mode for users to practice questions without scoring.
5. User Feedback and Analytics
  Feedback System: Allow users to provide feedback on questions or the game experience.
  Analytics Dashboard: Provide an admin dashboard to analyze user performance and game statistics.
6. User Interface Enhancements
  Responsive Design: Ensure the game is playable on various devices (mobile, tablet, desktop).
  Themes and Customization: Allow users to choose different themes or customize the gameâ€™s appearance.
  Animations and Effects: Add animations and visual effects to enhance the user experience.
7. Notifications and Alerts
  Achievement Alerts: Notify users when they achieve a milestone or high score.
  Daily Challenges: Introduce daily or weekly challenges with special rewards.
  Email Notifications: Send email notifications for game updates or user activities.
8. Database and Backend Improvements
  Data Security: Implement security measures to protect user data and prevent unauthorized access.
  Backup and Recovery: Set up automated backups for the database to prevent data loss.
  Scalability: Optimize the backend to handle a growing number of users and questions.
9. Integration with Other Services
  Social Media Sharing: Allow users to share their scores or achievements on social media.
  APIs: Integrate with external APIs for additional features like random question generation or trivia data.
10. Localization and Accessibility
  Multiple Languages: Provide support for multiple languages to reach a wider audience.
  Accessibility Features: Implement features for users with disabilities, such as screen reader support and keyboard navigation.

